    "Question": {
      "content": "Calculate the current in the loop of 15 turns and radius of 20 cm if the magnetic field generated is \\(1.4 \\times 10^{-3} \\, \\text{T}\\)",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "10A",
        "20A",
        "150A",
        "160A"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "20A"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Using Ampère's law for a solenoid: \\( B = \\mu_0 n I \\), where \\( n = \\frac{N}{2\\pi r} = \\frac{15}{2\\pi \\times 0.2} \\approx 11.94 \\, \\text{turns/m} \\). Solving for \\( I \\): \\( I = \\frac{B}{\\mu_0 n} = \\frac{1.4 \\times 10^{-3}}{(4\\pi \\times 10^{-7})(11.94)} \\approx 20 \\, \\text{A} \\)."
    },
